HEADWORD: bordered
<hw>bor"dered</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>having a border especially of a
specified kind; sometimes used as a combining term; <as>as,
black-<ex>bordered</ex> handkerchief</as>. Antonym of
<ant>unbordered</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>boxed</stype>;
<stype>deckled, deckle-edged, featheredged</stype>;
<stype>lined</stype>; <stype>seagirt, sea-girt</stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>finite</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

